reviews.text:
This request stop on the Atlantic Coast line between Par and Newquay

Timetable, shelter and two  benches are there as well as a bike stand

Stairs from the road or cycle access by some houses - timetable is there two

Service is operated by great Western Railway and the service is reliable

Information point and a sign saying which is the direction of travel

As it is a request stop signal to the driver you wish to board and make sure you are visible from the platform - if already on the train tell the conductor where you wish to get off - the guard/conductor will come up and down the train as all stops bar two are request stops

K3 is the timetable - available on line or at local manned stations

Single platform and single track line which explains the 2 hourly service but it is reliable
It's great! If you water long enough, a train will take you where you need to get.
